- **Why keep this:** it highlights a shift in the threat landscape where AI lowers the skill barrier for visually competent phishing

## Raw notes

- Low-friction AI tools raise the baseline for clean, conventional design in spam.
- People lose older visual heuristics for spotting fake messages as spam looks more polished.
- The practical risk is a lower skill barrier for scam and phishing operations.
- Generic AI-generated design patterns may become a "trust smell" over time.
- HN discussion points to weak incentives in free email systems as the deeper issue, not just AI.
- Attackers can copy real branded emails rather than generate new ones — the problem spans generation quality and distribution/filtering.

