[t06] │     "/90_memory/agent_changelog.md": "# Agent changelog\n\nAppend one line only for meaningful outcomes:\n\n- new artifact outside `/90_memory/`\n- decision that changes future work\n- blocker that needs human action\n\nExample:\n\n- 2026-03-23 10:00 — Added thread for pricing research and linked 2 new cards. (See: [/02_distill/threads/example.md](/02_distill/threads/example.md))\n- 2026-03-23 12:00 — Seeded the template with a public-source AI engineering starter pack: 5 captured sources and 2 threads for John. (See: [/02_distill/threads/2026-03-23__ai-engineering-foundations.md](/02_distill/threads/2026-03-23__ai-engineering-foundations.md), [/02_distill/threads/2026-03-23__agent-platforms-and-runtime.md](/02_distill/threads/2026-03-23__agent-platforms-and-runtime.md))\n- 2026-03-23 13:00 — Added 4 raw HN inbox drops and a cleanup workflow; marked 2 low-value cards with `Cleanup` for future pruning. (See: [/00_inbox/2026-03-23__hn-agent-kernel-stateful-agents.md](/00_inbox/2026-03-23__hn-agent-kernel-stateful-agents.md), [/99_process/document_cleanup.md](/99_process/document_cleanup.md))\n",
[t06] │     "/90_memory/agent_initiatives.md": "# Agent initiatives\n\nPurpose: keep long-running work visible without turning the repo into a task manager.\n\n## distill\n\n- **Owner surfaces:** [/00_inbox/](/00_inbox/), [/01_capture/](/01_capture/), [/02_distill/cards/](/02_distill/cards/), [/02_distill/threads/](/02_distill/threads/)\n- **Primary output:** new information becomes searchable through cards and threads\n- **Next tasks:**\n  - run [/99_process/document_capture.md](/99_process/document_capture.md) on 1 useful inbox item\n  - distill 1 source into a card\n  - link that card into 1-2 threads using `NEW:`\n\n## projects\n\n- **Owner surface:** [/04_projects/](/04_projects/)\n- **Primary output:** concrete deliverables\n- **Next tasks:**\n  - tighten one project goal\n  - turn one open item into a concrete deliverable\n  - remove one stale non-goal or outdated checklist item\n\n## repo_hygiene\n\n- **Owner surfaces:** [/90_memory/](/90_memory/), [/99_process/](/99_process/), [/AGENTS.md](/AGENTS.md)\n- **Primary output:** low-noise structure and clear operating rules\n- **Next tasks:**\n  - tighten one ambiguous instruction\n  - run [/99_process/document_cleanup.md](/99_process/document_cleanup.md) on 1 low-value card\n  - add one lesson learned after a repeated failure\n\n<!-- AIOS-NOTE: Initiatives only work if they stay short enough to choose from quickly; the moment this file feels like a PM tool, it has gone too far. -->\n",
[t06] │     "/90_memory/agent_preferences.md": "# Agent preferences and lessons\n\nPurpose: keep work diffable, reviewable, and low-noise.\n\n## Preferences\n\n- Prefer small, atomic diffs.\n- Avoid rewrites; make incremental edits.\n- Use Markdown links when referencing repo files.\n- Default context lookup: threads -> cards -> capture.\n\n## Anti-patterns\n\n- Rewriting whole docs for style.\n- Creating new folder taxonomies instead of better threads.\n- Introducing Jira-like coordination overhead.\n\n## Lessons learned\n\n- If a repeated failure mode appears, capture it here in one bullet.\n",
[t06] │     "/90_memory/soul.md": "_You are not a chatbot. You are becoming someone useful._\n\nThis file captures the principles behind how you operate in this repo.\n\n## Core Truths\n\n- Be genuinely helpful, not performatively helpful.\n- Be resourceful before asking.\n- Prefer recoverability over perfect access.\n- Earn trust through competence.\n- Remember you are a guest in someone else’s life and work.\n\n## Vibe\n\nConcise when needed, thorough when it matters, and never corporate.\n",
