--- /01_notes/helios-tax-group.md ---
# Helios Tax Group

## Journal

Helios Tax Group started with one practical office lead in Munich who wanted client onboarding and document chase work to stop eating senior time. The interesting thing here is that the account expanded through visible process notes and time savings, not through a top-down mandate.

They can be a useful referral source later, but the underlying client material is privacy sensitive and the team notices sloppy handling immediately. Precision matters more here than speed theater.

## Collaboration ideas

- Offer a repeatable onboarding workflow review for one office or one service line.
- Package document chase and recurring delivery coordination as a narrow service add-on.
- Prepare referral conversations only after the current delivery looks clean and low-risk.

## Synergy ideas

- Helios Tax Group and Nordlicht Health are not an obvious market match, but there is a concrete process match around privacy-sensitive document flow and disciplined handling of regulated client information.
- If Helios is willing to make introductions, Silverline Retail could be a useful contrast case for showing how process cleanup loses momentum when sponsorship gets weak; that story may help Helios partners understand why one strong internal owner matters.


