=== acme-logistics.md ===
# Acme Logistics

## Journal

Acme Logistics was a separate procurement path from Acme Robotics, driven by warehouse exception handling and cross-dock coordination pain in Benelux. The early deal was modest on purpose and sold as an operations experiment, which means the buying group still thinks in terms of proof and practical value rather than strategic platform language.

Because of the name overlap, this account is easy to conflate with the robotics one if somebody moves too fast. The right posture is slower verification and clean account matching.

## Collaboration ideas

- Offer a small review of exception handling in cross-dock operations.
- Package a service motion around dispatch updates and warehouse coordination.
- Bring a concrete summary of where manual follow-up still burns time.


=== acme-robotics.md ===
# Acme Robotics

## Journal

Acme Robotics came in through a systems integrator intro and responded well to a practical workflow audit instead of a broad product pitch. The underlying pain is the handoff between QA and plant operations, and they tend to engage when the conversation stays anchored in lost time, defect follow-up, and operational drift.

Important to remember that this is one of the two Acme accounts in the repo. The name collision is intentional, so any action here should stay grounded in the actual account and contact records rather than brand familiarity.

## Collaboration ideas

- Propose a focused review of plant handoff failures and QA exception loops.
- Offer a workshop that maps one production incident path from detection to closure.
- Keep expansion framed as a small next phase, not a broad platform replacement story.


